🧩 Phase 1: Planning & System Design (Day 1–2)
🎯 Goal:

Define what you are building before writing code

Tasks:
Finalize features (based on simplified version)
Identify roles:
Teacher
Student
Draw system flow:
Login → Dashboard → Quiz → Result
Create basic UI wireframes (rough sketches)
📦 Deliverables:
Final feature list
User flow diagram
Basic UI layout
💡 Tip:

Keep flows linear and simple — no branching complexity

🗄️ Phase 2: Database Design (Day 2–3)
🎯 Goal:

Design a clean and scalable database

Tables:
users
quizzes
questions
responses
results
Tasks:
Define fields (id, relationships, constraints)
Set foreign keys:
quiz → teacher
question → quiz
response → student
📦 Deliverables:
ER Diagram
Final schema
💡 Tip:

Avoid over-normalization — keep it practical

⚙️ Phase 3: Backend Setup (Day 4–6)
🎯 Goal:

Build core logic (brain of your app)

Tech:
Node.js / Express (or Django if you prefer)
Features:
User authentication (login/register)
Role handling (teacher/student)
CRUD for quizzes & questions
API for quiz attempt
Auto evaluation logic
📦 Deliverables:
REST APIs:
/auth
/quiz
/attempt
/result
💡 Tip:

Test APIs using Postman before frontend

🎨 Phase 4: Frontend Development (Day 7–10)
🎯 Goal:

Build user interface (React / Next.js)

Pages:
Login / Register
Dashboard (role-based)
Create Quiz (Teacher)
Attempt Quiz (Student)
Result Page
Tasks:
Build reusable components
Connect APIs
Add form validations
📦 Deliverables:
Fully working UI connected to backend
💡 Tip:

Don’t overdesign — clean UI > fancy UI

⏱️ Phase 5: Core Features Implementation (Day 11–13)
🎯 Goal:

Add features that make your project stand out

Features:
⏳ Timer with auto-submit
🔀 Random question order
🚫 One attempt restriction
📊 Instant result calculation
📦 Deliverables:
Fully functional quiz flow
🧪 Phase 6: Testing & Debugging (Day 14–15)
🎯 Goal:

Make your project stable

Test:
Login/logout
Quiz creation
Quiz attempt
Edge cases:
timer expiry
refresh page
invalid inputs
📦 Deliverables:
Bug-free working system
💡 Tip:

Test like a user, not a developer

🚀 Phase 7: Optimization & Polish (Day 16–17)
🎯 Goal:

Make your project look professional

Improvements:
Loading states
Error handling
Clean UI spacing
Responsive design
📦 Deliverables:
Smooth user experience
📑 Phase 8: Documentation & Viva Prep (Day 18–19)
🎯 Goal:

Prepare for evaluation

Tasks:
Finalize:
SRS / PRD
ER diagram
Architecture diagram
Prepare answers:
Why RBAC?
Why simplified design?
Trade-offs made
📦 Deliverables:
Project report
PPT